812
00:34:26.565 --> 00:34:29.777
[Eva] Elle Woods. W-O-O-D-S.

813
00:34:29.860 --> 00:34:31.904
-Buttery blonde--
-Mom. Mom. I'm here.

814
00:34:31.987 --> 00:34:33.155
I'm here.

815
00:34:33.238 --> 00:34:35.574
Oh. my God. Oh.

816
00:34:35.657 --> 00:34:36.909
[whispers] I'm sorry.

817
00:34:38.076 --> 00:34:39.620
I am fine.

818
00:34:39.703 --> 00:34:41.371
Are you okay? Do you know who I am?

819
00:34:41.455 --> 00:34:42.623
-Yes. yes.
-What's your middle name?

820
00:34:42.706 --> 00:34:44.082
I am fine. It's just a bump.

821
00:34:44.166 --> 00:34:48.212
Honey. what were you thinking?

822
00:34:48.295 --> 00:34:51.840
Sweetie. people die
in mosh pits every day.

823
00:34:51.924 --> 00:34:54.718
Well. here I am. Alive.

824
00:34:54.802 --> 00:34:57.429
And who is
that handsome young gentleman who seems

825
00:34:57.513 --> 00:34:59.348
very concerned about your well-being?

826
00:35:00.349 --> 00:35:01.975
He's just a friend.

827
00:35:03.811 --> 00:35:04.978
She's gonna make it.

828
00:35:05.979 --> 00:35:07.147
Thanks.

829
00:35:09.983 --> 00:35:11.235
And thank you for helping.

830
00:35:11.318 --> 00:35:13.779
Oh. yeah. [stammers] See you later.

831
00:35:13.862 --> 00:35:15.280
See you.

832
00:35:15.364 --> 00:35:16.281
[Eva sighs]

833
00:35:19.493 --> 00:35:22.746
The minute I heard
the venue was called CarpetMart.

834
00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:25.499
I knew the night would end in the ER.

835
00:35:27.459 --> 00:35:28.877
Wait. you got me the tickets?

836
00:35:29.795 --> 00:35:31.505
Oh. sweetie.

837
00:35:31.588 --> 00:35:33.632
Your dad may be spending
more time in the kitchen.

838
00:35:33.715 --> 00:35:35.926
but that doesn't mean
he suddenly knows how to cook.

839
00:35:39.638 --> 00:35:40.973
I'm glad you're here.

840
00:35:41.056 --> 00:35:43.058
[contemplative music playing]

841
00:35:46.812 --> 00:35:51.316
So. about my performance
at Robin's the other night. I...

842
00:35:51.400 --> 00:35:53.944
you know. I probably should've
just said I liked the book

843
00:35:54.027 --> 00:35:56.363
instead of... you know.

844
00:35:56.446 --> 00:35:59.032
Comparing discrimination
to a bad nose job?

845
00:36:00.909 --> 00:36:03.620
I get it.
You're just trying to connect with people.

846
00:36:05.247 --> 00:36:07.249
[sighs] It's been really hard here.

847
00:36:08.333 --> 00:36:11.920
I mean. I've never not been liked before.

848
00:36:12.004 --> 00:36:13.422
I hate it.

849
00:36:13.505 --> 00:36:16.550
Okay. let me let you in
on a little something.

850
00:36:16.633 --> 00:36:18.302
High school is hard.

851
00:36:18.385 --> 00:36:21.096
For everyone. no matter where you live.

852
00:36:22.097 --> 00:36:23.265
But you

853
00:36:23.348 --> 00:36:26.602
are going to win over
this entire city before you know it.

854
00:36:26.685 --> 00:36:28.604
[indistinct chatter nearby]

855
00:36:28.687 --> 00:36:30.272
[nurse] Let me grab those charts.

856
00:36:30.355 --> 00:36:32.357
Ten percent off
any procedure at my husband's

857
00:36:32.441 --> 00:36:35.903
